{#- ### Top Mitigations — single-table P1+P2 view for the Management Summary.
    Inputs:
      groups    : list of { header, include_affects_column, mitigations[] }
                  After M3.10 this is always a single group with header=None.
                  Each `mitigations[i]` carries
                    { id, title, component_list[{id,name}], primary_component_id,
                      addresses[{ref,label}], effort, priority }
      intro     : top-of-section paragraph string (mentions §9 register)
      footer    : optional italic footer line under the table (may be None)

    Schema of the rendered table (Priority FIRST column):
      | Priority | Mitigation | Component | Addresses | Effort |
        - Priority: bold P1/P2 marker — table is sorted P1 → P2.
        - Mitigation: `[M-NNN](#m-nnn) — <title>` (link only on ID, title plain).
        - Component:  backtick-joined component IDs (comma-separated).
        - Addresses:  one finding per line, `[F-NNN](#f-nnn) — <weakness>`.
        - Effort:     Low / Medium / High.
-#}
### Top Mitigations

{{ intro }}
{% for g in groups %}
{%- if g.header %}
#### {{ g.header }}

{% endif -%}
| Priority | Mitigation | Component | Addresses | Effort |
|---|---|---|---|---|
{%- for m in g.mitigations %}
| **{{ m.priority }}** | [{{ m.id }}](#{{ m.id | lower }}) — {{ m.title }} | {% if m.component_list %}{% for c in m.component_list %}`{{ c.id }}`{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% else %}—{% endif %} | {% for a in m.addresses %}[{{ a.ref | replace('T-', 'F-') }}](#{{ (a.ref | replace('T-', 'F-')) | lower }}){% if a.label %} — {{ a.label }}{% endif %}{% if not loop.last %}<br/>{% endif %}{% endfor %} | {{ m.effort }} |
{%- endfor %}
{% endfor -%}
{%- if footer %}

{{ footer }}
{% endif %}
